<h1>Problem 1768 - 2024 China Mathematical Olympiad, P4 of 6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Let \(a_1, a_2, \dots, a_{2023}\) be nonnegative real numbers such that \(a_1 + a_2 + \cdots + a_{2023} = 100\). Let \[A = \{(i, j) \vert 1 \leq i \leq j \leq 2023, a_ia_j \geq 1\}.\] Prove that \(\lvert A \rvert \leq 5050\) and determine when equality holds.</p>
